If it wasn't for you, I'd still be stuck in Cazador's kennels. So, thank you. For being that evil bastard.
Gods. There really is no justice in the world.

EditorData.NodeContext: Genuinely bummed out

Text.Value: The parasite must be playing with my ears, because I was sure that beardy tramp told you to find the Heart of the Absolute and then blow yourself up.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Gale Avatar is speaker, his bomb is a surprise to us

Text.Value: It is not the time to chat - move!

EditorData.NodeContext: Racing through a collapsing dimension, trying to reach the dream figure 'Daisy'
EditorData.logicalname: Topic 45 - in Astral Plane during INT - before Gith fight

Text.Value: We probably should save the druid, though. He does have his uses.
I swear, druids care more about the plants of this land than the people.
Still, it's good to know she's more likely to attack you face on, rather than stabbing you in the back.
Still, let's hope it doesn't come to that!

EditorData.NodeContext: A little nervously - Gale's ability to explode worries him

Text.Value: And if she does chase me - will you stand with me?
I know they're your people, but I still don't love walking into a den of killer gith warriors.
Honestly? I don't love walking into a den of killer gith warriors.
You gave up your father to have freedom? An understandable decision. Sacrifices must be made, after all.
Wyll gave up his father to have freedom? An understandable decision. Sacrifices must be made, after all.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 137 - Wyll chose to sacrifice his father so he could get out of his pact

Text.Value: Not yet, but it will become my concern very quickly if a pissed-off god-queen sends a legion of warriors after you.
I don't want to get into it now.
Sorry - did you want something? Or just looking for a distraction?
Cazador liked to toy with people too. Let them think there was hope right until the end. Until he snatched it all away.

EditorData.NodeContext: a dark memory

Text.Value: I just hope what you got was worth all of this.
For the Lady of Loss, she does not like losing.
Your devil's a sly little wretch, I'll give her that.
Wyll's devil is a sly little wretch, I'll give her that.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 107 - Released Mizora from pod in COL

Text.Value: Maybe it's just hard to see someone else suffer the same thing. It feels unfair - like justice denied.
Better a dagger at my throat than fangs, Astarion.
Now, what do you want, exactly?
Even a wet rag like Zevlor deserved a better death than that.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 185 - Didn't save Zevlor from the Colony, entered Wyrm's Crossing, camped

Text.Value: Just stay focused on slaying the Infernal, will you? The undead have it hard enough already.
I just hope he stays focused on battling Infernal forces. The undead have it hard enough already.
I know the look is meant to be very 'murder' heavy, but it's a bit much. Even for me.
So, Mystra's requested a chat with Gale? Unusually polite for a god.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 106 (NOT GALE) - Elminster tells Gale Mystra wants to Talk

Text.Value: You almost pity Orin, taking Minthara like that. Give her half a chance and she'll gut the shapeshifter like a fish.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 127 - Orin kidnapped Minthara from camp

Text.Value: If you want to sell your soul, be my guest.
What in the nine Hells is going on? I thought we had him!

EditorData.NodeContext: Defeated the Big Boss Ketheric, but he has now retreated to the Colony, and the party saw a giant tentacle burst through the roof of the Tower. High intensity situation.

Text.Value: Both? I don't know. It's complicated.
Not if I can help it.
Do not jest about slaying my kin, elf.
We keep hunting for answers. What other choice do we have?

EditorData.NodeContext: response to 'what do you suggest?'

Text.Value: Pain can break anyone, but you bore it well and got what you wanted.
Pain can break anyone, but she bore it well and got what she wanted.
Paint a picture, it'll last longer.
Do you often burst into flames or was that a special occasion?
No need to be shy, this is a good thing.
And maybe this will help him relate to you a little better. You're both sporting horns now, after all.
I've killed my fair share of people, but wiping out an entire building with a cannon powered by the sun?

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 30 - You blew up the Creche

Text.Value: So, Gale's agreed to be a good boy and hand the Crown over to Mystra?

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 180 - Com. Gale agreed to return Crown to Mystra

Text.Value: The blood, the screaming - just thinking about it makes me smile.
Well. That will take some time to process.

EditorData.NodeContext: Big "Wow, that escalated quickly" vibes.

Text.Value: And now it's offering us power. If we're willing to 'evolve'.

EditorData.NodeContext: 'evolve' = turn into mind flayers

Text.Value: This is no ordinary mind flayer parasite. Who tampered with it and why? What do they have planned for us?
Defying Mystra, declaring that you'll rule the Karsite Weave - Gale my boy, I didn't know you had it in you.
Defying Mystra, declaring that he'll rule the Karsite Weave - I didn't know Gale had it in him.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 179 - Av. Gale wants to keep Crown, become god

Text.Value: I'm almost tempted to tell Shadowheart what she did. To see if I can jog her memory.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 167 - COMP SH on Shar path killed parents, memories removed

Text.Value: All your past, just wiped clean. I don't know if I'm horrified or jealous.
That's the spirit! Chin up and all that.
Not for his wit or wisdom - he'll just make an excellent shield if we're attacked.
He's not. We still have options.
Fine. If you don't want to hear the truth, I can't force your ears open.
Come on, you can't say you weren't a little curious to see what would happen?

EditorData.NodeContext: playfully, as if trying to worm a guilty secret out of you

Text.Value: I much prefer it when I'm the one prowling in the shadows, about to strike.
Protection is protection - I'll take whatever I can get.
I can imagine.
At least my lack of tentacles. I'm not sure what's next for you.

EditorData.NodeContext: Player's turned partially into a mind flayer

Text.Value: Not that they don't look flattering on him. Almost everything does.
Hedging your bets with Mystra, I see? I can't say I blame you.
So, Gale's hedging his bets with Mystra. I can't say I blame him.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 178 - Av. Gale didn't agree to return Crown of Karsus to Mystra

Text.Value: I can't believe Orpheus wants one of us to transform.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 131 - Should player become a MF

Text.Value: Do not jest about slaying my kin, vampire.
I hope you're right, but I don't like this. He's playing with us.

EditorData.NodeContext: 'this' = having met a devil that seems to know more about our situation than we do

Text.Value: I wonder how he does it. Why he does it.

EditorData.NodeContext: Stress on 'why'

Text.Value: All I wanted was to get a worm out of my head - I didn't sign up for dimensional travel and murderous gith.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 28 - Back from Astral Plane, dealt with Inquisitor

Text.Value: I really thought you and Shadowheart might fight to the death over that artefact.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 119 - Lae'zel and Shadowheart fought (LZ avatar - peaceful outcome)

Text.Value: Given that a hag couldn't solve our wriggling little problem, he might be right.
It took a little time, but you got there.
It took a little time, but she got there.
You almost pity Orin, taking Lae'zel like that. Give her half a chance and she'll rip out the shapeshifter's spine.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 125 - Orin kidnapped Lae'zel from camp

Text.Value: Also, she'll want to cave his skull in and, honestly, I would not mind seeing that.
Although maybe you're used to it? I imagine this feels just like home.
Still, it's done. That's what matters.
I'm fine with either, naturally. The last thing I want is to ruin these nails digging through rock.
Just like that hulking bear to stomp off in a huff.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 168 - ShadowCurse not lifted, Halsin Gone

Text.Value: I hope you don't make a habit of betraying your travelling companions.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 111 - Shadowheart sold out by party to Viconia

Text.Value: Of all the places you've dragged me, this might just be the most foul.
We're not his playthings - we'll show him that.
So, we have the hammer. Now all we have to do is...
Shadowheart's parents are at peace. And so's she, it seems.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 166 - COMP SH Mercy-killed her parents in Act 3, abandoned Shar in Act 2

Text.Value: No matter what Jaheira says, immortality is a difficult drug to kick.
Who'd want to hold a power like the Crown of Karsus in their hands, just to hand it to someone else?
Oh, will you? Because you've got it all figured out, I'm sure.

EditorData.NodeContext: Annoyed

Text.Value: Given our shared affliction, I suppose you had a similar dream...?

EditorData.NodeContext: fishing for confirmation of something he already believes to be true

Text.Value: You're right, I don't understand. You have a choice, but it sounds like you're actually considering this.
'Shop around', he said. He seems sure we won't find anything.
We should tell Aylin that Lorroakan is hunting her. She has a right to know.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 155 - Lorroakan wants to revive Nightsong

Text.Value: Maybe, but he's not the only one spinning a web for us.

EditorData.NodeContext: Wary

Text.Value: Hardly a luxurious setting, but it definitely has its upsides for a vampire.
Gods...

EditorData.NodeContext: Standing on the streets of Baldur's Gate, looking at them in the sun with new wonder.

Text.Value: One the one hand, killing Gortash would be fun. On the other, Halsin can be very annoying.
And he might be right. We've had no luck so far.
I almost preferred it when we were worried we might transform at any moment.
What do you mean? You'll be there by my side, won't you?
Not again, at any rate.
I did.
Not that I wouldn't understand - respect it even - but it does leave one a little nervous.
We have to figure out what's happening. Why we aren't changing, what's planned for us, and why a devil is suddenly taking an interest.
He made his choice. That's not on me.
I don't like it. This whole thing feels like a trap.
If we can answer those questions, we might have a chance. And if not - well, we'll be exactly where this Raphael wants us.
Tell me I misheard, Gale. Because how would that make sense? How would that even be possible?
Even if you've damned yourself to a lifetime of that same pain.
Even if she's damned herself to a lifetime of that same pain.
I won't lie, I'm a little impressed.
I want to be clear - letting Minthara tag along with us was your idea. So if you wake up with a dagger to your throat, that's on you.
I don't care what he's offering - I wouldn't have been so quick to sign with the devil.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 146 - Signed the deal with Raphael in SC

Text.Value: Gods, lighten up. Enjoy a joke, it won't kill you.
Still considering our options?
Explain the Netherese orb and the terrible power within you.
So, we owe our continued survival to a rebel squid and a prisoner prince.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 46 - in Astral Plane during INT - met Emperor

Text.Value: So much for the cavalry riding to our rescue.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 86 - Resolving ambush at Danthelon's Dancing Axe in WYR

Text.Value: I see. So... pretty far, then?
Being willing to turn away from what he knew and bending the darkness to his will? Wonderful to see.
It does...
Some of us reach for freedom, while others just grow to love their chains, I suppose.

EditorData.NodeContext: Disappointed - he's watching Lae'zel bow to her version of Cazador

Text.Value: This is the first time in two hundred years I've seen these streets in the sunlight.

EditorData.NodeContext: Standing on the streets of Baldur's Gate, looking at them in the sun with new wonder.

Text.Value: Did you actually want something, or are you just here to spoil my fun?
The parasite must be playing with my ears, because I was sure that beardy tramp told Gale to find the Heart of the Absolute and then blow himself up.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Gale Avatar is NOT speaker, his bomb is a surprise to us

Text.Value: He reminds me of - well, someone I used to know. Someone that liked to play with people.

EditorData.NodeContext: He's talking about Cazador

Text.Value: I'm sorry, but this is what happens when we trust your people: they strap you to a machine and try to kill you.
This is what happens when you trust the gith: they strap you to a machine and try to kill you.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 176 - Comp. saw Avatar use Zaith'isk in CRE

Text.Value: Gods, I never though I'd be so relieved to find a light in the darkness.
No... No, I don't think that's it.
I know enough of it. I've lived enough of it. But if you won't hear me, that's on you.

EditorData.NodeContext: stress on 'lived'

Text.Value: Still, I don't like being under anyone's thumb. The sooner we can turn the tables and start pulling their strings, the better.

EditorData.NodeContext: stress on 'their'

Text.Value: So, you stood up to the Dark Lady? I'm almost impressed.
So, Shadowheart stood up to the Dark Lady? I'm almost impressed.
And our cranial guests already came with some advantages - maybe there're more to uncover.
And a waste of a perfectly good Gale, I suppose.
You misheard.
Oh, can we? Because you've got it all figured out, I'm sure.

EditorData.NodeContext: Annoyed

Text.Value: This is what we get for putting our faith in a network of spies, I suppose.
We'll have to cross that bridge when we come to it.
I did not go to the Hells and back because I like his company - if anyone has to make the sacrifice it should be him.
I was sure I saw you with one of our more magical, and more valuable, items earlier. Any idea where it is now?
And who knows, they might even have some new tricks to reveal?
Most people would have held on to that scroll for as long as they could bear to. And probably a century or two longer than that.
If Wyll survives long enough to enjoy it.
If you survive long enough to enjoy it.
If it's Mystra's will, anything is possible.
So, we kill Gortash or Halsin dies? It's not an easy call.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 126 - Orin kidnapped Halsin from camp

Text.Value: I don't trust it. We should avoid using these powers.
Present company excluded, of course. You can be murderous as you like.
You could watch out for anyone acting strangely, but... well, you know the lunatics we camp with.
Come on, let's finish this.
Gods, really? Saving a drow I can understand, but saving gnomes?

EditorData.NodeContext: Doesn't think much of gnomes

Text.Value: Shadowheart. Shadow Heart...

EditorData.NodeContext: Rolling the name around in your mouth, trying it on for size

Text.Value: So what do we do?
When the devils start approaching you, you know you're in deep.
I really thought Shadowheart and Lae'zel might fight to the death over that artefact.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 128 - LZ and SH Fought - Comp - Peaceful Outcome

Text.Value: Not if I can avoid it.
Once his kind has you under their thumb, they won't ever let you go.
Credit where it's due: you are tenacious. And tougher than I expected.
Credit where it's due: Shadowheart is tenacious. And tougher than I expected.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 164 - SH Freed her Parents after Abandoning Shar in Act 2

Text.Value: But of course, I wouldn't want to pry.
I'm still thinking about Karlach. About what she said.

EditorData.NodeContext: Heard karlach give a big, emotional speech about how she's going to die
EditorData.logicalname: Topic 130 - Karlach finished her monologue after Gortash's death, where it became clear she's going to die (Companion)

Text.Value: I mean, of course I'll support you. I'd just rather do it from a distance. Because of the... explosion.
And it's a powerful weapon to boot? Things are starting to look very interesting...
Cazador, my old master, liked to toy with people too. Let them think there was hope right until the end. Until he snatched it all away.

EditorData.NodeContext: a dark memory
EditorData.logicalname: Not Wyll/Warlock & Doesn't know Cazador Master

Text.Value: Won't be long now. They'll pay for what they did to me.

EditorData.NodeContext: thinking about killing the mind flayers - low-level anger
EditorData.logicalname: Topic 63 -  END - going to Morphic Pool

Text.Value: So, you've agreed to be a good boy and hand the Crown over to Mystra?
So, Gale's agreed to be a good boy and hand the Crown over to Mystra?

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 177 - Av. Gale agreed to return Crown of Karsus to Mystra

Text.Value: Not that I approve of goblins, of course - filthy little beasts - but I do like a good den of debauchery.
Some people just don't appreciate the wonders the world has to hold, I suppose.
And who knows? Maybe we'll have better luck with our next weapon of incomprehensible destruction.
Hmm? Oh - yes, your trademark wit.
I hope it was the right call.
I was trying to think of something more profound to say, but no. It just 'kind of sucks.'
I doubt Shar would take kindly to anyone meddling in her little project, though.
So, you chose your family over your god.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 165 - AVATAR SH Freed her Parents after Abandoning Shar in Act 3

Text.Value: Then again, you'd have to be mad to spend your days marching through this gloom.
Unless she chose it herself. Which is even more worrying, honestly.
We're not all as messed up as you.
So, that's how the legend ends. The Blade of Frontiers, cast down to the Hells.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 110 - Wyll died when Mizora was anihilated in her pod in the Colony

Text.Value: That being said - when you do explode, how far away should I be?

EditorData.NodeContext: coming off the back of the previous sincere-sounding line

Text.Value: So, if you don't want to discuss the truth, what do you want from me?
I know you said there's a cure here - I just hope it's not 'decapitation'.
They probably think decapitation is a perfectly reasonable 'cure'.
The gith probably think decapitation is a perfectly reasonable 'cure'.
I knew you were tough, but a killer?
I could tell Shadowheart was tough, but a killer?
They do look pretty good, don't they?
I knew it! There's no shame in being curious about power. It is exhilarating.
I can't even tell if any of you are acting strange because you've been replaced or because this group is full of weirdos.
It reminds me of Cazador, taunting his slaves with hope when he knew the game was rigged.

EditorData.NodeContext: a dark memory

Text.Value: Must you? Does Gale's will not come into it?
I don't know if Faerûn needs another hero, but you seem happy. I suppose that counts for something.
I don't know if Faerûn needed another hero, but Wyll seems happy. I suppose that counts for something.
Now, was there anything else?
We probably should save the wizard, though. He does have his moments.
Then find a way to avoid it.
Of course not, darling! You mustn't blame yourself.
Or however this sordid tale ends. I wouldn't want to presume.
Inconceivable as it might be, I actually didn't ask you.

EditorData.NodeContext: Still a little lost in the moment

Text.Value: I suppose we can spare the occasional trinket if it stops you from killing us all.
Not that I mind you sticking a thumb in your slaver's eye, I just like to keep track of who wants us dead.
It's just a waste of a perfectly good cult that we could be controlling.
I wish I could tell you dying isn't so bad, but my experience has been quite... specific. Sorry.

EditorData.NodeContext: trying to cheer her up, realises he's failing badly

Text.Value: One the one hand, killing Gortash would be fun. On the other, Gale can be very annoying.
You know, I never dreamed our noble Jaheira would be such a terrible, terrible mother.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 89 - Speaking to Jaheira's family in Lower City

Text.Value: So, you finally saw the light and turned on your mistress.
So, Lae'zel's finally seen the light and turned on your mistress.
So, Lae'zel's finally seen the light and turned on her mistress.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 141 - Vlaakith appeared in camp as a hologram and Lae'zel was on Orpheus path after

Text.Value: But that's a problem for the future. What are we doing now?
I expected Nightsong to be overjoyed after killing her 'fair-haired fool'.
So, Shar's chosen walks among us. How lucky we are.
Actually I'm not really clear on what we have to do, but I assume we're smashing something.
At least you showed it what you thought of its offer. Nicely done.

EditorData.NodeContext: Player stamped on tadpole the mind flayer offered them, killing it

Text.Value: Haha! That's - oh, you're serious.

EditorData.NodeContext: "That's hilarious", but cut off. Astarion genuinely thinks the player was joking with "we can't leave him to die"

Text.Value: It's all right. I'm all right.
You might not be able to outfox him, but I will.
I was always more of a 'lurker in', historically.
And in this case, they're enemies we might not see coming until it's too late.
To think, he's had that orb within him this whole time and never told us.
You have been dealt a difficult hand, my friend. I'm sorry.

EditorData.NodeContext: Sincere tone

Text.Value: If the shapechanger wants Gortash dead, then let's kill Gortash and get Yenna back.

EditorData.logicalname: Topic 52 - Orin kidnapped someone from camp

Text.Value: So, what shall we talk about?
Or to see so many Harpers clanking about.
I do admire how you got that lantern, you know.
Or it's... undersides? Because it's - you know what I mean.

Synopsis: Astarion's Topical greetings - once-off introductions to his default InParty dialog that play depending on the location/recent events in the game.
